<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Help: Content</title>
  </head>

  <body bgcolor="#ffffff"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" >
  <HR ALIGN="center" SIZE="1">
    <h3><center> HOW TO INSERT A NEW ARTICLE OR HOW TO EDIT EXISTING ARTICLES</center></h3>
    <h4><center><a href="content.html.de">deutsche version</a></center></h4>
<HR ALIGN="center" SIZE="1">
<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="red">
<center>After you have inserted your article, click <STRONG>einf&uuml;gen</STRONG> or <STRONG>speichern</STRONG> at the bottom of the page!</center>
</font>
<p>
      <a name="thema"><b>
      thema</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	A 'Thema' is a category, e.g. 'Residenzpflicht'. If a category is chosen here, 
	the article is being produced automatically into this category.</font>
    </p>
    
     <p>
      <a name="artikelart"><b>
      artikelart</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	Artikelart classifies the article in a hierarchical way. The 'feature' is the lowest one. Combined with a 'Thema' it appears on the startpage and the themepage. But as soon, as a new one is produced, the older one is pushed downwards. Without a 'Thema', it appears only on the startpage. A 'startspezial' is the leading article of the startpage, which stays as long on the first position, as a new 'startspezial' is produced. A Startspezial should not be connected to a theme. 'Themenspezial' is the leading article on the themepages. It appears only on the assigned themepage. Always assign a theme to it! </font>
    </p>
   
   
     <p>
      <a name="title"><b>
      haupttitel/untertitel</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	The 'Haupttitel' ist the main title of the article, situtated above the article in big 
	letters. The 'Untertitel' is a second title, which may be 255 characters long. it is 
	situated in between 'Titel' and 'Abstract'</font>
    </p>
    <!--  
    <p>
      <a name="datum"><b>
      datum</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	As 'Datum' should always be entered the date, when the article is being inserted to the dataspace
	The current date is alway already inserted. In exceptional cases, articles may be date back.
	A date has to be entered in the form <i>yyyymmdd</i>.
	</font>
    </p>
	-->
	    <p>
      <a name="ort"><b>ort</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	'Ort' are geographical places. Never use things like 'worldwide'. 
	The 'Ort' is always being published just in front of the title.</font>
    </p>

    <p>
      <a name="urheber"><b>urheberIn</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	'UrheberIn' means author. An author indicated in the textfield has priority 
	over an author chosen from the popup-menu. Enter a group name or look
	 for groups in the popup-menu, if your text is not written by a single person. Publishing real names is a sensible matter.</font>
    </p>
    
 <p>
      <a name="contact"><b>kontaktinfos</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	contact informations might be published here. Keep in mind the sensibility of such data!<br>
	</font>
    </p>
    
  <p>
      <a name="abstract"><b>abstract</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	An abstract is a short, preliminary text, being situated before the content of the article.
	 it should roughly outline what the article is about. it is a sort of teaser and may attract people to read on.<br>
	</font>
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <a name="inhalt"><b>inhalt / html</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	The main content. The button 'html' may be checked, if you use HTML-data. 
	The default is ascii (normal) text. In the case of HTML, delete all unnecessary french quotings
	( '>', '<') and the header and footer part of the HTML-file.
	<br>
	</font>
    </p>
 
    <p>
      <a name="comment"><b>kommentar</b><br>
    <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	An internal comment is useful to communicate with other people using the production system, e.g. an article is not yet ready and therefore should not be published or an articel has been changed . Use this function to raise teamwork!</font>
    </p>
 <!--
    <p>
      <a name="termin_name"><b>termin name</b><br>
	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	Ist ein Terminname angegeben, so erscheint dieser in der rechten
	Navigation auf den Startseiten, ansonsten wird der wirkliche Titel 
	der Nachricht verwendet.</font>
    </p>

    <p>
      <a name="oldstyle"><b>oldstyle</b><br>
	  <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
      Der Umschaltknopf <i>oldstyle</i> gibt an, ob es sich um automatisch
      eingespielte Daten aus dem alten Aktuell-System handelt, bei einer
      entsprechenden Bearbeitung von Nachrichten aus dem alten System 
      sollte der Knopf deselektiert werden (und freigeschaltet) selektiert.
 	  </font>
    </p>
-->
    <p>
      <a name="freigeschaltet"><b>freigeschaltet</b><br>
      <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1">
	  This button signifies if the article will be uploaded with the next production
	   from the dataspace into the www. It may be unchecked again, so in the next production 
	   this article is not any longer in the www.
	</font>
    </p>


    <hr>
    <address><a href="mailto:webdb-l@mail.nadir.org">webdb-l@mail.nadir.org</a></address>
  </font>
  </body>
</html>
